# Mind Mate AI

**Mind Mate AI** is a compassionate, AI-powered mental health companion built in Python.  
It provides empathetic conversation, mood tracking, and curated mental health resources — all from your terminal.

> **Disclaimer:** Mind Mate AI is not a substitute for professional mental health care.  
> If you are in crisis, please contact a helpline immediately (e.g. text HOME to 741741 or call/text 988).

---

## Features

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| �� AI Chat | Empathetic conversation powered by OpenAI GPT |
| 📊 Mood Tracker | Log your daily mood on a 1–5 scale with optional notes |
| 📚 Resources | Curated mental health resources filterable by category |
| 🖥️ CLI | Simple, distraction-free command-line interface |

---

## Requirements

- Python 3.9+
- An [OpenAI API key](https://platform.openai.com/api-keys)

---

## Installation

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/ahmed7arbi55/Mind_Mate_AI.git
cd Mind_Mate_AI

# Install in editable mode with dev dependencies
pip install -e ".[dev]"
```

---

## Configuration

Set your OpenAI API key as an environment variable:

```bash
export OPENAI_API_KEY="sk-..."
```

---

## Usage

Start the interactive CLI:

```bash
mind-mate
# or
python -m mind_mate_ai.cli
```

### Commands

| Command | Description |
|---|---|
| `/mood` | Log your current mood |
| `/history` | View mood history summary |
| `/resources` | List all mental health resources |
| `/resources <category>` | Filter resources (`crisis`, `general`, `mindfulness`, `professional`, `support`) |
| `/clear` | Clear the conversation history |
| `/help` | Show help message |
| `/quit` | Exit the app |

